full_summary:
# Government Tender Announcement

## Open Construction Source List for 3 Wing Bagotville

### Invitation to Tender

Defence Construction Canada (DCC) invites contractors and suppliers to apply for inclusion in the Open Construction Source List (OCSL) for the Department of National Defence at 3 Wing Bagotville, Quebec, and its satellite sites. The OCSL will be used for commercial, residential, industrial, institutional, and civil work required by the Department for Fiscal Years 2023-2024, 2024-2025, and 2025-2026.

### Terms and Conditions

*   Contractors and suppliers interested in being included in the OCSL must submit a request through this MERX posting by January 23, 2023.
*   DCC requires ten (10) business days to process an application for the OCSL.
*   Applicants must choose their preferred official language (English or French).
*   The OCSL will be used for construction services with an estimated value of $10 million and below.
*   Contractors and suppliers on the OCSL will be invited to bid on work opportunities that arise.
*   The OCSL may be used for procurements covered by trade agreements to which Canada is a party.

### Requirements and Security

*   Contractors and suppliers shall meet the requirements outlined in the solicitation/tender documents.
*   Contracts awarded by DCC may include measurable performance standards and requirements.
*   DCC reserves the right to establish other source lists for specific categories of construction services.
*   The OCSL may be used for procurements covered by trade agreements to which Canada is a party.
*   Contractors and suppliers must meet the security requirements as outlined in the solicitation/tender documents.

### Disclaimer and Notice

*   DCC reserves the right to reject any application that does not demonstrate that the contractor or supplier has met the stated requirements.
*   DCC may publish quarterly an Advance Procurement Notice (APN) identifying potential tenders with anticipated security requirements.
*   Contractors and suppliers who apply to be placed on the OCSL consent to the disclosure of their legal name, address, and the inclusion in the OCSL being made public.

### Contact Information

*   Defence Construction Canada
*   Jacob Lachapelle, Senior Project Manager
*   Jacob.Lachapelle@dcc-cdc.gc.ca
*   Phone: (343) 550-4560
*   Address: 2030 boulevard Pie-
